<Layout>
  <h1>From Cross Key Drive to the Digital Frontier.</h1>

  <Section title="The Story">
    <p>
      Cross Key Studios started with a simple idea: that the web should be built
      by hand. The vision first took shape while our founder was living at his
      mother-in-law's house, where we realized that the modern web was leaving
      people behind. While developers on expensive rigs and fiber-optic lines
      don't notice the weight of a heavy site, the average user on an older
      device certainly does. We saw a need for a human touch to ensure that
      quality web experiences aren't a luxury. Named after the street where it
      all began, this studio remains dedicated to the craft of inclusive,
      efficient web development.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="The Approach">
    <p>
      We don't hide behind a library or a framework; we write the code that runs
      your site from scratch. Much like a tailored suit, a hand-coded website
      fits your business perfectly without the bulk of "off-the-rack" solutions.
      By avoiding heavy libraries and redundant plugins, we create platforms
      that are faster, more secure, and significantly less likely to crash.
      Every line of CSS is written with a specific purpose, which eliminates the
      headache of code conflicts during future updates. This meticulous process
      ensures that your digital presence is lean, mean, and built to last.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="The Studio Philosophy">
    <p>
      Cross Key Studios was born from the realization that the modern web has
      become dangerously bloated. Statistics show that nearly 40% of users will
      abandon a website that takes more than three seconds to load, yet most
      templates are packed with unused code that slows everything down. Using a
      template is like trying to build a house with a Swiss Army knife; it might
      work in a pinch, but it isnâ€™t the right tool for a professional result. We
      stripped away the heavy plugins and the "good enough" shortcuts to return
      to clean, purposeful engineering. We refuse to compromise on delivering a
      site that prioritizes your content and brand using the smallest, most
      efficient code possible.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="The Human Element">
    <p>
      Based in San Antonio, we work with forward-thinking brands both locally
      and globally. While we take pride in our Texas roots, our focus remains on
      providing a boutique experience that large agencies simply can't
      replicate. We are a small, focused studio, which means you won't be passed
      off to a junior account manager. When you work with us, you speak directly
      to the architects building your site from the first line of code to the
      final launch. This direct partnership ensures that your vision is never
      lost in translation.
    </p>
  </Section>

